Emergency treatment of headache.
 Headache is a frequent presenting complaint in the emergency department.
 Once a diagnosis is established, and significant organic disease can be ruled out, relief of pain must be addressed.
 Referral for follow-up care and narcotic habituation is a recurrent problem for the emergency physician.
 This article discusses the differential diagnosis of headache, evaluation of the emergency room patient, and treatment of the patient with headache.
